Back in 2008, we had an awake article and the article was entitled, can the problem

00:08:32.059 --> 00:08:35.940
of crime be solved?

00:08:35.940 --> 00:08:41.059
That was February 2008.

00:08:41.059 --> 00:08:51.620
And the writer of the article, Criminal Mind, was written by a doctor Stantonese, same

00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:55.259
now.

00:08:55.259 --> 00:09:01.779
And in the article, it told us to consider the example of a woman who had been molested

00:09:01.779 --> 00:09:04.220
as a child.

00:09:04.220 --> 00:09:10.059
She took up drugs, she abused alcohol, used tobacco.

00:09:10.059 --> 00:09:20.259
And at the time that the article was written, she was serving a life sentence in prison.

00:09:20.259 --> 00:09:24.179
But while in prison, she began to study with us.

00:09:24.179 --> 00:09:30.539
See that prison circumstance changed her vantage point and her viewpoint.

00:09:30.539 --> 00:09:39.139
And anyhow, she studied with us and she took the heart which she was learning.

00:09:39.139 --> 00:09:46.860
And the article says, now she's no longer a slave to destructive thinking and vices.

00:09:46.860 --> 00:09:56.659
One of her favorite Bible texts is 2 Corinthians 3, 17, which states, now Jehovah is the Spirit.

00:09:56.659 --> 00:10:03.299
And where the Spirit of Jehovah is, there is freedom.

00:10:03.299 --> 00:10:06.779
So we love the people out there.

00:10:06.779 --> 00:10:10.700
That's why we don't give up in our efforts to help them.

00:10:10.700 --> 00:10:16.299
That's why we keep getting in our midweek meeting, this encouragement to keep preaching

00:10:16.299 --> 00:10:26.799
and to have a positive attitude because we don't know who or what kind of individual

00:10:26.799 --> 00:10:31.240
we're going to be talking to at each door.

00:10:31.240 --> 00:10:34.639
And so we should always have that positive attitude.
